Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Bumrah again opens the door for India! Nathan McSweeney's hard resistance comes to an end and Australia lose their second wicket. Bumrah continues and steams in from over the stumps, uses the crease to his benefit and bowls it from a bit wide angle and slants it on the off-pole, on a hard length. Nathan McSweeney is drawn forward to defend it out, but the ball kisses the surface and just nips away and bounces a bit more. Hence, McSweeney plays inside the line and a healthy outside edge is found. Rishabh Pant does the rest behind the wickets by taking a regulation catch. Bumrah gets his second and McSweeney departs for 39 off 109 balls. Australia trail by 89 runs.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Nitish Kumar Reddy gets a big wicket here! India finally gets the breakthrough that they were craving for here. This is short of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne decides to take it on. He frees his arms and tries to steer it away which got him a few boundaries in this session. This is slower through the air, full and on off, goes straight, Marsh plays for the turn in and prods forward to block. The ball takes the slightest of outside edges behind where Rishabh Pant grabs it well. There is a slight appeal, and Marsh starts to walk back. The umpire raises the finger after seeing it.
